         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_e036c24b30087b320e3fca53ff974d23">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates of Religious Orders, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_ae96988e5cb3651c8201943e0070b819">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Some materials included in this collection indicate the provenance of the following collections: Karl Hofberger of Starnberg, Germany, and Baron Gunnar Trönnberg of Sweden.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_0aa9795f6d9be1d9446dc9af373f6574">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains bookplates of various religious orders in the Christian tradition. Dating from the 16th to the 18th century, many of the bookplates represent Catholic communities or organizations in Germany.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_5c00c5b39d836e073a6cb9590043ece0">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bookplates – Religious Orders. II. Bookplates – Cities. III. Bookplates – Unidentified.</p>
         <p>The original filing system grouped materials either by religious order or by the location of specific communities and organizations. Because of the small size of this collection, this original system has been maintained and is reflected in the series divisions. Within each series, folders are arranged alphabetically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
